  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Connected Speech Decoder drill (reductions like gonna/wanna/whatcha)",
  "description": "Add a new listening drill page 'Connected Speech Decoder' that trains users to understand reduced/linked forms of natural spoken English (e.g., 'gonna'→'going to', 'whatcha doin''→'what are you doing', 'lemme'→'let me', 'didja'→'did you', 'kinda'→'kind of'). Each question plays TTS audio of a short casual phrase containing one or more reductions, and the user must type (or pick) the fully-expanded standard form. This targets a specific listening-comprehension gap not covered by existing Minimal Pairs, Listen & Summarize, or Dictation drills — decoding *reduced* natural speech rather than single-phoneme discrimination or full sentence dictation.\n\nBackend (app/routers/connected_speech.py, new): endpoints `GET /api/connected-speech/session?difficulty=easy|medium|hard&count=8` returns a session of N items. Items are generated by the LLM via `app/services/llm.py` with a seeded prompt asking for JSON `[{reduced: str, expanded: str, hint: str, category: 'gonna'|'wanna'|'yaknow'|'whatcha'|'other'}]`, or, to avoid per-session LLM cost, seed from a small curated JSON bank under `app/data/connected_speech_bank.json` (~60 items across categories) and shuffle. TTS for `reduced` uses existing `app/services/tts.py` (play casual/natural voice). `POST /api/connected-speech/attempt` accepts `{item_id, user_answer, reduced, expanded, correct, time_ms}`, normalizes and grades (lowercase, strip punctuation, allow contraction equivalents via a small equivalence table), persists to a new table `connected_speech_attempts(id, user_id, reduced, expanded, user_answer, correct, category, time_ms, created_at)` via `app/dal/connected_speech.py`. `GET /api/connected-speech/stats` returns accuracy per category for the dashboard.\n\nMigration: add to `_MIGRATIONS` in `app/database.py`:\n  `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS connected_speech_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, user_id INTEGER, reduced TEXT NOT NULL, expanded TEXT NOT NULL, user_answer TEXT NOT NULL, correct INTEGER NOT NULL, category TEXT, time_ms INTEGER, created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);`\n(Pure new table, no ALTER needed.) Also add matching SCHEMA entry.\n\nFrontend: new page `frontend/src/pages/ConnectedSpeechPage.tsx` with phases select→listen→answer→feedback→summary. Play button (replays audio up to 3x — counter shown), text input with submit, per-item feedback showing reduced spelling, expanded form, and category tag. Summary shows accuracy, per-category breakdown, and a 'reveal all' list. Register route in `frontend/src/App.tsx` as `/connected-speech`, and add a launcher card on the Home page under listening drills (follow existing card pattern used by Listen & Summarize / Minimal Pairs).\n\nRationale: reductions are the #1 reported reason intermediate learners fail to understand native speech; no existing drill in the app targets this explicitly. Small, self-contained, and reuses TTS + LLM infrastructure.",
